properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 1 at 3:26AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
Patchy Dense Fog has developed across portions of south central
Wisconsin west and southwest of Madison in the Mineral Point,
Shullsburg and Monroe areas. Visibilities in spots have dropped to
one quarter mile or less.

Motorists in these areas are urged to slow down and drive with
extra caution, as visibilities will vary significantly given the
patchy nature of the fog. Use low beams, reduce driving speed, and
allow for plenty of room between you and other cars.

The patchy dense fog may spread into the Janesville and Madison
early this morning as well. Temperatures are right around
freezing, so isolated slick spots may develop on untreated
roadways.

The patchy dense fog should begin to burn off between 6 am and 8
am CST.

NWSheadline: PATCHY DENSE FOG IN SOUTH CENTRAL WISCONSIN EARLY THIS MORNING
